Have you ever been required to wear a skirt?
Adam Taha
Writing about life experiences · Author has 5K answers and 94.4M answer views · 6y ·

Yes, at a ceremony.

In our community, men wear skirts for relaxing, sometimes for festivals. Back home, men wear them every time, going to work, studying and for even working as farmers.

As you can see..some lads thought they’d have a go..

And here’s how they do it with the full bling…and as you can tell, they are not smiling because probably, their dad said..

“If you don’t wear these skirts I will fuck you up. Now don’t get your mum upset and wear it right NOW!”…

So for me, I was young, aged 12, and one day they wanted to initiate me into the fully cultural custom but the thing is, I really didn’t give a shit about it. I did everything opposite, a rebel and that is how I have always been.

But mum won’t have it.

Dad won’t have it either, and my aunt won’t have it and so my uncles. They wanted me to get used to it before they leave, fly to England and leave me behind until I also fly over.

The festive season came and so they thought it was a good time to get it sorted.

You can then imagine me running through the streets, dodging them as they tried catching me to put some coloured vibrant skirt on.

After they caught me, brought me into house, they got me to wear it. It was plain white but more stripped colour like what these lads are wearing..

After wearing one, I thought..

“Hey, this is alright. I dig this. Looks kind of cool and I don’t feel hot under sun as I usually do.”

So in our community, we always wore skirts but when in England, the men just wear them for relaxing at home or when they all together, chilling..

Now if I can introduce this wave to gangs and all those guys who wear jeans so way down below their asses, I might be onto something and create a new trend, where it looks cool…

And you can even replace the suit and just have shirt tie, shoes with the skirt….
